					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold deposited with the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of the village for maintaining a perpetual lamp in the temple of Maṇavāḷa-Perumāḷ at Tiruviḍavandai in Paḍuvūr-nāḍu a subdivision of Āmūr-kōṭṭam, by Nakkaṉ Ēnādi the headman of Innambar on the northern bank situated in Śōṇāḍu. The inscription has been assigned to <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> (<hi rend="bold">M.E.R.</hi> 1911, Part II, para. 19).</p>						

						</summary>
